            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Instagram: 8-15 targeted hashtags (30 maximum). TikTok: 3-5 highly relevant tags. LinkedIn: 3-5 professional tags. X (Twitter): 1-2 contextual tags. Facebook: minimal impact, 1-2 if used at all. These counts reflect platform algorithm preferences, not arbitrary limits.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Should you use the same hashtags every time?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>No. Rotating hashtags prevents spam classification by algorithms and enables testing which combinations drive the most reach and engagement. Build 3-4 hashtag sets per content pillar and rotate them between posts.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Do hashtags still work in 2026?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
